So equation: 2*(2π - t) = (π - t) + (t - π) Simplify: 4π - 2t = 0 ⇒ 4π = 2t ⇒ t = 2π But t = 2π is outside the interval (π/2, π]. No solution here. t in (3π/2, 2π): Arccos(cos t) = 2π - t, Arcsin(sin t) = t - 2π, Arctan(tan t) = t - 2π. Equation: 2*(2π - t) = (t - 2π) + (t - 2π) Simplify: 4π - 2t = 2t - 4π Bring variables to left and constants to right: 4π + 4π = 2t + 2t ⇒ 8π = 4t ⇒ t = 2π Again, t = 2π is the boundary, not included. No solution. t in (π, 3π/2): Arccos(cos t) = t - π, Arcsin(sin t) = π - t, Arctan(tan t) = t - π. Equation: 2*(t - π) = (π - t) + (t - π) Simplify: 2t - 2π = π - t + t - π ⇒ 2t - 2π = 0 ⇒ t = π But t = π is the boundary, not included. No solution. t in (0, π/2): All functions equal to t. No solution. t in (3π/2, 2π): Same as above, no solution. So Case 2 also has no solution.
